Given two strings:ransomNote and magazine. Return true if you can construct ransomNote using the letters in magazine.
Each letter in magazine can only be used once. All letters are lowercase English letters.

Approach: Frequency Counting
Since letters can only be used once, we must count how many times each character appears in magazine.
For each character in ransomNote, check if it exists in the counted frequencies.
If yes → decrease its count. If at any point the count becomes negative → return false.
If we finish checking → return true.

class Solution {
    public boolean canConstruct(String ransomNote, String magazine) {
        if (ransomNote.length() > magazine.length()) {
            return false;}
        int[] count = new int[26];
        for (char c : magazine.toCharArray()) {
            count[c - 'a']++;}
        for (char c : ransomNote.toCharArray()) {
            count[c - 'a']--;
            if (count[c - 'a'] < 0) {
                return false;}}
        return true;}}
